net.sf.jclec.mo.problem.dtlz

Class DTLZ6ParallelEvaluator

  • java.lang.Object

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, net.sf.jclec.IConfigure, net.sf.jclec.IEvaluator, net.sf.jclec.JCLEC, IMOEvaluator

    public class DTLZ6ParallelEvaluator
extends MOParallelEvaluator
    Parallel evaluator for DTLZ6 optimization problem. For a definition of the DTLZ6 problem, see:

    Paper: K. Deb, L. Thiele, M. Laumanns, E. Ziztler. "Scalable test problems for evolutionary multi-objective optimization". Evolutionary Multiobjective Optimization, pp. 105-145. 2005.

    HISTORY:

    • (AR|JRR|SV, 1.0, March 2018) First release.

    Version:
    1.0
    Author:
    Aurora Ramirez (AR), Jose Raul Romero (JRR), Sebastian Ventura (SV)

    Knowledge Discovery and Intelligent Systems (KDIS) Research Group: http://www.uco.es/grupos/kdis

    See Also:
    MOParallelEvaluator, DTLZ6Objective, Serialized Form

      • configure

        public void configure(org.apache.commons.configuration.Configuration settings)

        Parameters for MOParallelEvaluator are:

        • objective (List of Objective): The list of objectives to be evaluated. Parameters for every objective are:
          • [@min] (double): Minimum value, negative infinite by default.
          • [@max] (double): Maximum value, positive infinite by default.
          • [@maximize] (boolean): Objective to be maximized (true) or minimized (false).
